Linus and Luke discuss Ubisoft’s surprising delay of its earnings report and halted trading, sparking speculation about major financial trouble or a possible sale. They reflect on Ubisoft’s long history of mismanagement, industry consolidation, and what it means for Canada’s shrinking tech and gaming landscape.

Linus and Luke discuss Valve’s confusing decision to name the new Steam Controller exactly the same as the old one, arguing that it harms searchability, repairability, and basic clarity. They compare it to Apple’s notorious naming issues and insist that manufacturers should never reuse identical product names when clearer alternatives like “Steam Controller 2” exist.
